      "type": "action",
      "name": "Splurting Slime",
      "system": {
        "actionType": {
          "value": "action"
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The mutant troll is in its Mutated Split form, and both halves are within 30 feet of each other</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The duplicated beings spray mutated flesh and organs toward each other, absorbing most of the pieces but raining down acidic viscera on any creatures caught in the 10-foot-wide line between them. These creatures take @Damage[8d8[acid]] damage with a @Check[reflex|dc:27] save. The troll can't use Splurting Slime again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Splurting Slime]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 1}.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 2}.</p>",
